results.definition: impelled by physical force especially against resistance
examples: a real cop would get physical

results.definition: according with material things or natural laws (other than those peculiar to living matter)
examples: a reflex response to physical stimuli
the physical characteristics of the earth
the physical size of a computer

results.definition: having substance or material existence; perceptible to the senses
involving the body as distinguished from the mind or spirit
examples: was sloppy about everything but her physical appearance

results.definition: relating to the sciences dealing with matter and energy; especially physics
